Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.99,0:00:14.78,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I've reached my limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:15.74,0:00:17.85,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,My limit as a Soul Reaper, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.71,0:01:54.80,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew about you since\Nyou were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.07,0:01:58.63,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.83,0:02:03.38,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,You were special from the\Nmoment you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.72,0:02:07.06,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,That's because you're\Na human and...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.47,0:02:15.90,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,You talk too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.82,0:02:18.79,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Aizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.96,0:02:34.08,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,D-Dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.51,0:02:42.48,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, say something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.13,0:02:45.80,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Dad...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.49,0:02:52.11,B2,,0000,0000,0000,,Ow!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.43,0:02:56.53,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That was close!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.25,0:03:00.10,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.87,0:03:09.29,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Keeping his distance, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.87,0:03:11.17,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,A wise decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.48,0:03:21.47,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,You've been watching\Nfor quite a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.21,0:03:24.10,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Gin.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.17,0:03:28.98,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I haven't just been watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.35,0:03:32.98,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I just couldn't find an opportunity\Nor a need to help you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.43,0:03:35.44,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.38,0:04:18.19,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.97,0:04:25.89,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I won't\Nbe holding back.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.38,0:05:00.48,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Raikoho.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.67,0:05:05.79,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's been a while...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.94,0:05:10.33,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,since I've fought you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.79,0:05:17.80,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you remember the\Nlast time we fought?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.68,0:05:23.94,B2,GIN (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Oh, this isn't good.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.59,0:05:57.17,B2,GIN (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Unacceptable.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.42,0:06:02.74,B2,GIN (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A guardian of the gate isn't supposed\Nto open the gates.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.82,0:06:06.82,B2,GIN (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A gatekeeper who lost isn't\Nopening any gates.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.37,0:06:12.57,B2,GIN (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When a gatekeeper loses,\Nit means... "death."{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.78,0:06:25.20,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,When I slashed Jidanbo's arm, you\Ngot all mad and attacked me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.52,0:06:27.40,B2,ICHIGO (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}What the hell are\Nyou doing?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.57,0:06:38.58,B2,GIN (FLASHBACK),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Impale him, Shinso!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.12,0:06:55.40,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I remember thinking of you\Nas an interesting kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.16,0:06:59.73,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.60,0:07:05.36,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Liar.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.91,0:07:07.53,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you trying to taunt me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.19,0:07:09.41,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,That's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.86,0:07:12.31,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not saying that I don't\Nremember your sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.65,0:07:14.87,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't remember your heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.68,0:07:17.70,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever I face an opponent,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.70,0:07:19.63,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I can slightly tell what my\Nopponent is thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.14,0:07:22.79,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I can't read their minds,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.16,0:07:26.00,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,but I can tell why they're fighting,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.00,0:07:29.03,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,what they want from me,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.03,0:07:30.76,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,or whether they're looking\Ndown on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.72,0:07:36.49,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,During battle, I'm desperate, so\NI usually notice it after it's over,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.49,0:07:41.53,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,but the stronger my opponents are, the\Nstronger their hearts are conveyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.01,0:07:44.77,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You're quite the poet.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.32,0:07:46.35,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.03,0:07:51.19,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You have none of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.65,0:07:57.02,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Even when you were fighting me,\Nyou weren't looking at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.35,0:08:01.43,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know what you were\Nlooking at, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.07,0:08:05.25,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.71,0:08:08.52,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you were\Nan interesting kid,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.52,0:08:10.88,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,but you're actually kind of creepy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.37,0:08:17.45,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You're one to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.14,0:08:23.19,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I can understand why Captain\NAizen is interested in you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.86,0:08:29.43,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know how far my\NShinso can extend?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.20,0:08:31.36,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,No, I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.72,0:08:33.93,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,The length of a hundred swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.55,0:08:39.08,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,When I was little, people used to say\NI carried a set of hundred swords.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.70,0:08:41.04,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.46,0:08:45.04,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Then do you know how far\Nit can extend in Bankai?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.63,0:08:48.00,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come here to be quizzed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.42,0:08:50.98,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,What, you give up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.98,0:08:52.28,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,How boring.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.82,0:08:54.13,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Oh well.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.13,0:08:58.10,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you in measurements\Nthat you can understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.54,0:09:01.18,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Thirteen kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.99,0:09:06.31,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Must be hard to imagine just from\Nhearing the numbers, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.73,0:09:07.56,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,So let me demonstrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.15,0:09:09.29,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.29,0:09:10.94,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,This time, I'm not holding back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.72,0:09:16.01,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Bankai...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.90,0:09:19.41,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Kamishininoyari.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.38,0:09:54.21,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Why do you look surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.32,0:10:01.45,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way a Bankai couldn't\Nstop another Bankai!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.55,0:10:11.95,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You know...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.55,0:10:15.01,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You really are a creepy kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.93,0:10:42.49,B2,RANGIKU,0000,0000,0000,,Gin?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.82,0:10:48.33,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,How scary.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.02,0:10:54.84,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I better deal with you while I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.80,0:10:58.09,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Otherwise, things may\Nget troublesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.89,0:11:02.64,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}When did his sword shrink?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.37,0:11:05.44,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Did I get distracted\Nand miss it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.22,0:11:10.35,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}No, I never took my attention\Naway from his sword.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.74,0:11:13.15,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}There's no way that I couldn't have\Nseen a sword that long shrink.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.75,0:11:18.08,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Now then... What should I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.34,0:11:21.32,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You easily stopped my Bankai.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.16,0:11:24.78,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I guess I have no choice\Nbut to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.26,0:11:38.21,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's an impressive sword.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.21,0:11:41.13,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I feel like mine will break\Njust from attacking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.34,0:11:42.69,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.69,0:11:44.81,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Then why don't you\Nbreak already!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.05,0:11:49.62,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If my hunch is correct, he\Nonly shrunk his sword.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.62,0:11:51.02,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He hasn't ended\Nhis Bankai.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.35,0:11:56.19,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}If my hunch is correct...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.27,0:12:00.03,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Once he points that\Ntip at me, it's over!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.41,0:12:22.76,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}At this distance...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.45,0:12:30.91,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.13,0:12:41.63,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,The scariest thing about\Nyour Bankai's ability
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.63,0:12:44.03,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,is not its length or its\Ndestructive force.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.26,0:12:47.05,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,But its contraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.01,0:12:50.41,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I was thinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.50,0:12:54.02,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Telling me about its length\Nserves no purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.45,0:12:57.03,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, not telling me about it\Nwould be to your advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.14,0:13:02.81,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Swinging your sword and slicing\Nup the town serves no purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.50,0:13:06.41,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, attacking me head on\Nwould be to your advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.54,0:13:15.06,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You showed me those things to distract\Nme from its contraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.18,0:13:17.44,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.94,0:13:19.90,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Wow...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.56,0:13:26.77,B2,GIN (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He noticed that in my first attack\Nand dodged my second attack.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.02,0:13:28.65,B2,GIN (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}How scary...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.65,0:13:30.97,B2,GIN (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}He still has room\Nfor improvement.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.04,0:13:37.73,B2,GIN (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}But he's not good\Nenough, yet.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.47,0:13:40.23,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Since you've figured it out,\NI guess I have no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:45.34,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you how fast Kamishininoyari\Ncan extend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.14,0:13:50.35,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.64,0:13:52.31,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's 500 times that speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.49,0:13:58.39,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Kamishininoyari isn't the\Nlongest Zanpakuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.97,0:14:00.98,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the fastest Zanpakuto.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.42,0:14:04.59,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Even if you know that, you\Nhave no chance of winning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.01,0:14:28.32,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.66,0:14:31.04,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,You're getting slower.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.58,0:14:32.85,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Are you already at your limit?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.44,0:14:36.23,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it seems like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.99,0:14:38.81,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I've reached my limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.54,0:14:41.81,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,My limit as a Soul Reaper, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.37,0:14:44.27,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.91,0:14:46.81,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,My soul is going to\Nbe restructured.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.94,0:14:51.20,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.92,0:14:55.12,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hogyoku's will is finally
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.66,0:14:58.31,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,beginning to understand\Nmy thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.77,0:15:14.87,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Concentrate.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.82,0:15:17.64,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Ignore his swinging attacks.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.15,0:15:20.14,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Pay attention to when\Nhe makes a thrust.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.10,0:15:23.23,B2,ICHIGO (M),0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Don't let him point\Nit at me!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.87,0:15:29.19,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Just kidding.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.34,0:15:41.54,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You're too jumpy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.77,0:15:43.84,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.20,0:15:46.04,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I swear I'll break your sword!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.48,0:15:49.01,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Fine. Try it if you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.55,0:16:03.54,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I've reached my limit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.53,0:16:06.64,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,My limit as a Soul Reaper, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.37,0:16:10.19,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.61,0:16:16.20,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hogyoku's will is finally beginning\Nto understand my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.65,0:16:18.01,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of nonsense is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.62,0:16:20.16,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.20,0:16:24.12,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that the Hogyoku\Nhas a will of its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.92,0:16:27.75,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,That sounds like\Nnonsense to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.27,0:16:30.09,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I can't blame you for being\Nunable to sense it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.96,0:16:37.29,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Even I didn't know the Hogyoku had its\Nown will until becoming its master.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.33,0:16:42.21,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think the\NHogyoku's power is?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.79,0:16:45.73,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the power to dominate
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.81,0:16:50.23,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,two opposing forces-the boundary between\NHollows and Soul Reapers?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.87,0:16:51.82,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.77,0:16:56.14,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hogyoku's true power
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.66,0:17:02.08,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,is the ability to manifest the\Ndesires of those around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.45,0:17:03.58,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.11,0:17:05.47,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.91,0:17:09.43,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I'm saying that the miracles\Nthat happened around
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.43,0:17:13.33,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Ichigo Kurosaki, Rukia Kuchiki,\Nand Kisuke Urahara
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.33,0:17:17.23,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,were all manifested by\Nthe Hogyoku's will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.12,0:17:20.56,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.83,0:17:25.97,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The reason why Kisuke Urahara mistakenly\Nbelieved that the Hogyoku's power
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.97,0:17:28.35,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,was the power to control\Nthe boundary between
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.35,0:17:32.40,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Hollows and Soul Reapers is because,\Nas its creator, that is what he desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.92,0:17:38.32,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Rukia Kuchiki passed all of her spiritual\Npowers to Ichigo Kurosaki
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.92,0:17:41.49,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,and lost her Soul Reaper powers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.99,0:17:48.63,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,because she was still suffering from\Nthe pain of killing Kaien Shiba.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.99,0:17:56.09,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Yasutora Sado and Orihime Inoue\Ndeveloped special powers
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.76,0:18:02.13,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,because deep in their hearts, they\Nhated being considered helpless.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.94,0:18:11.31,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I knew about the Hogyoku's\Ntrue power.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.36,0:18:16.80,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,No, I suppose it's incorrect\Nto say that I knew about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.40,0:18:20.00,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,More correctly, I knew that\Nits power was not the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.00,0:18:22.78,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,power to control the boundary\Nbetween Hollows
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.78,0:18:24.79,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,and Soul Reapers like Kisuke\NUrahara thought it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.90,0:18:26.75,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Because
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.90,0:18:30.53,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,if that was really its power,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.53,0:18:32.96,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Shinji Hirako and the\Nother Visoreds
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.96,0:18:35.92,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,would never have become\Ncomplete Visoreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.13,0:18:40.41,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hollowfication of\NShinji Hirako and the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.41,0:18:43.18,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,other Visoreds was a Hollowfication experiment
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.45,0:18:47.85,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,as well as a confirmation\Nof the Hogyoku's powers.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.93,0:18:52.65,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The experiment was a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.84,0:18:58.01,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Kisuke Urahara's activation\Nof the Hogyoku's power
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.01,0:19:01.40,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,evolved Shinji Hirako and\Nthe other Visoreds
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.40,0:19:02.78,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,into complete Visoreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.15,0:19:09.16,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,And I had a hypothesis on\Nthe Hogyoku's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.72,0:19:14.13,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I had Rukia Kuchiki go\Nto Ichigo Kurosaki.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.33,0:19:19.77,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Naturally, there are limits\Nto the Hogyoku's power.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.60,0:19:24.80,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hogyoku has the power to manifest\Nthe desires of those around it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.54,0:19:30.72,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,But if the target does not have\Nthe power to achieve it,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.72,0:19:32.23,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,nothing would happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.21,0:19:37.57,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,In that sense, it has the power\Nto guide you to your desires.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.22,0:19:42.70,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Living creatures are odd things.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.34,0:19:48.70,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,They're able to achieve\Ntheir petty wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.19,0:19:50.37,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.59,0:20:14.67,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You stopped that well.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.12,0:20:17.82,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty good for sheer luck.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.08,0:20:20.85,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you calling\Nlucky, stupid?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.17,0:20:23.00,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,I-Ichigo...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.38,0:20:24.89,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What is it?! Don't bother me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.65,0:20:28.21,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be able to handle him soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.55,0:20:29.70,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interfere!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.48,0:20:36.97,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, Captain Aizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.27,0:20:39.59,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Did I interrupt your conversation?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.54,0:20:41.42,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.63,0:20:48.22,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,I just finished talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:52.25,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.68,0:20:53.95,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.95,0:20:55.51,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,How should I know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.51,0:20:59.41,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea what was going\Non when you came flying in!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.41,0:21:00.69,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,And I still don't know\Nwhat's going on!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.19,0:21:02.88,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean\Nyou don't know?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.88,0:21:05.62,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,You're the one who's\Nbeen fighting him!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.62,0:21:07.26,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Stop complaining!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.26,0:21:10.58,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,If you want to know, ask Aizen\Nyourself, you pain in the ass!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.39,0:21:12.59,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.13,0:21:15.58,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,The Hogyoku is very\Naptly named!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.17,0:21:25.47,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,It has the power to destroy the wall\Nthat separates those who are gods
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:26.93,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,from those who aren't!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.44,0:21:42.48,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,So you've come...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.99,0:21:46.54,B2,AIZEN,0000,0000,0000,,Kisuke Urahara!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.46,0:23:23.33,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,You and your father are so alike.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.33,0:23:25.69,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,What? I'm nothing like this guy!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.69,0:23:30.46,B2,ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,No way! My son is nowhere\Nnear as good as me!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.46,0:23:32.26,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,See? That's what\NI'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.26,0:23:33.57,B2,ICHIGO / ISSHIN,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, right!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.94,0:23:36.76,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,The Arrancar Encyclopedia.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.63,0:23:40.98,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Today I'm going to talk about\Nmy Bankai, "Kamishininoyari."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.98,0:23:44.65,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,It can extend its blade\Nup to 13 kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.22,0:23:48.28,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Thirteen kilometers is difficult\Nto comprehend.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.28,0:23:51.42,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,It's the size of about\N39 Tokyo Towers.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.42,0:23:54.95,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,For Yammy... I'd say\Nabout 260 Yammys?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.33,0:23:56.41,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,Plus...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.24,0:23:58.00,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,Whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.60,0:24:00.59,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,If I ever forget anything,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.59,0:24:03.16,B2,GIN,0000,0000,0000,,I can retrieve it as long as it's\Nwithin 13 kilometers of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.16,0:24:04.58,B2,ICHIGO,0000,0000,0000,,H-How convenient.